                        <interp inst="t18411025-name-1256" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN THOMAS</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable M</hi> 237.) I searched the prisoner, and found five knives on his person, and this glass.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> These knives were given me on board the <hi rend="italic">George William,</hi> at the Commercial-dock—there was no one belonging to them—Mr. Hall, the ship's steward, said I might have them.</p>
               <p>(<hi rend="italic">The prisoner handed in a statement, partly in prose and partly in verse, representing that he had fought under the late Admiral Nelson in various actions, and begging for a lenient sentence.</hi>)</p>
